cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.ED, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the task of predicting the linguistic complexity of language learning materials, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses supervised machine learning models, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of different linguistic features, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of the models in a web-based language learning platform, which could be related to cs.ED (Education) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
